<doc id="982506" wikidata="Q17513015" url="?curid=982506" title="Army Aviation Badge (Philippines)">
<text>The Army Aviation Badge also known as the &quot;Philippine Army Aviator&#x27;s Badge&quot; is awarded by the Commander, Armor Division, PA to commissioned officers and enlisted aircrew of the Army Aviation Regiment, military officers and enlisted personnel attached to the Army Aviation Regiment, civilian personnel, foreign and local dignitaries. The badge is awarded to military personnel who qualify as military aviators and aircrew and are attached to the Army Aviation Regiment, PA.

==Description==
The badge is the Seal of the Philippine Army superimposed over a pair of silver wings.

